	<h4 id="6">Arabic Civilizations (Arabic Edition)</h4>
	<img src="ArabicCiv.jpg" class="float_l" width="250" height="auto"/>
	<p style="margin-left:270px;">
	The Arabian Peninsula (Al-Jazirah Al-Arabiya) has always been a center for many historical events. The Arabian Peninsula is known for its unique location on the most important main roads in the world between the East and the West. Throughout the times, many known civilizations with great impact on history arose in the region. Those civilizations are characterized by many advanced achievements that had a great impact on the development of mankind throughout history. The most prominent of which were the laws of rulers, laws systems, engineering sciences, astronomy, weather, medicine and surgery, architecture, construction of dams, and the construction of irrigation canals. In addition to enriching mankind with knowledge related to agriculture, industry, trade, and its sciences, the region was the source of the first foundations of writing. <br />

	Given a large number of successive civilizations in the Arab region and the difficulty of addressing them all, the book selects certain civilizations that had an important role in enriching humanity and whose effects are still visible today. Some of those civilizations include the Sumerian, Akkadian, Babylonian, Assyrian, Pharaonic, and Yemeni civilizations. The book also addresses other topics that greatly influenced the course of events in those civilizations; for example, the pre-Islamic era and Islamic caliphates such as the Umayyad, Abbasid, and Fatimid caliphates. The book also highlights the role of Arabs in carrying civilization to Andalusia and the role of Syriacs in the emergence of Arab civilization. Finally, the book acknowledges the role of women in the mentioned civilizations. <br />

	This book is based on established facts and information the author obtained through research in many approved Arab and foreign sources. The book is rich in knowledge not only in terms of history but also in terms of the relationship with religions and arts in the mentioned civilizations. The book also contains many maps and pictures that support the credibility of the content. The author hopes that this book can be used as a textbook in relevant universities, colleges, and institutes, in addition to being an asset for specialists in Arab civilization, antiquities, and culture.
	</p>
	<br />
